title: Third suspected arson set in West Seattle
text:
Investigators were called to the scene of another fire that may have been intentionally set in West Seattle.
It is the third suspected arson in four days and within a mile of a community center fire and two car arsons.
A homeowner who lives in the 6500 block of 40 th Avenue Southwest said that at about 3 a.m. Wednesday, two young men knocked on his door and said that his trash cans were on fire.
The homeowner called 911 and firefighters arrived.
Seattle police officers and fire investigators told KIRO 7 they believe the fire was another arson.
Early Monday, between 3 a.m. and 3:30 a.m., a community center less than a mile away also caught fire at 35th and Holly Street.
#breaking another suspected arson in West Seattle details at 430 live @KIRO7Seattle pic.twitter.com/RUsZYn7qr2
â€” David Ham (@HamKIRO7) October 21, 2015 ATF investigators were at the scene there trying to find out how it happened.
Early Sunday morning, investigators believe arsonists targeted two vehicles on Sylvan Heights Drive Southwest.
Those fires broke out between 4 a.m. and 4:30 a.m.
Investigators cannot say if the fires are connected or just unlucky coincidences.
